<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/83640460-diane-l"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/83640460-diane-l">Diane L</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    au contraire - I thought the ending was really well done. Stories don't always have tidy stop points. This strikes me as a perceptive rendition of a p<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    au contraire - I thought the ending was really well done. Stories don't always have tidy stop points. This strikes me as a perceptive rendition of a prevalent American paranoid attitude towards "exotics." The reader absolutely can defend either - or any other - speculation as to what happens next. I spent a little while trying to figure it out but then realized I didn't really need to.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
